		<!-- message -->
		<div>Brael,<br />
<br />
The item thing I understand the worry of exploitation but I don't think it would matter.<br />
<br />
If 2,000 users play on a given server, they all have to log out and in sometime, or zone. It is rare one person does not do one of the aforementioned every hour or so.<br />
<br />
The item database could be written in a way that whenever such things occured they'd automatically update. I think it would make it pretty difficult for someone to exploit that. <br />
<br />
If they kept a file, kinda like what Microsoft does with Windows on previous/past installations and settings, they could have the same thing for an item database. Kinda like if we had so and so settings on sunday and a patch was done on monday, then the item database list would have two sections, one past, and one present.<br />
<br />
The only problem I could see is that we'd zone in one day and have to wait 20 minutes to zone, but with proper notification as to what was going on I don't think it'd be a big deal.<br />
<br />
Some things bother me like the revamped Splitpaw and Mistmoore happening on Stormhammer, which is an obvious 2-3 hours I'm sure of time that we're also suffering, minus the content. This of course isn't the only drawback to serverwide patches.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		<!-- sig -->
			<div>
